{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880971999,"sessionID":"ses_28540a122ffeV6GyViz90QWuux","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac1110b001gYOwD12dLN6N93","messageID":"msg_d7ac105af001G8NB658P3wtjBe","sessionID":"ses_28540a122ffeV6GyViz90QWuux","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_8a7fcb6792984b0f94504e5f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 本提案实现 AgentCube 项目的 RBAC 配置，将 ServiceAccount、Role/ClusterRole、RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding 从 Helm Chart 模板中独立出来，形成可单独部署的 RBAC 配置模块。该 RBAC 配置是 AgentCube 控制平面组件的权限管理基础，支撑 Workload Manager 和 Router 的访问控制需求。\n6: \n7: 目标是：\n8: \n9: 1. **权限最小化** - 为每个组件分配精确的 RBAC 权限，遵循 least privilege 原则\n10: 2. **模块化部署** - RBAC 配置可独立于 Helm Chart 单独部署，支持预创建权限\n11: 3. **多租户支持** - 通过 Role/RoleBinding 支持 namespace-scoped 权限，实现多租户隔离\n12: 4. **审计友好** - 独立的 RBAC 配置便于权限审计和安全审查\n13: 5. **环境兼容性** - 支持开发、测试、生产环境的差异化权限配置\n14: \n15: 本实现基于 manifests/design.md 和 manifests/delta-spec.md 的规范，遵循 Kubernetes RBAC 最佳实践。\n16: \n17: ## Scope\n18: \n19: **Module:** manifests  \n20: **Language:** YAML  \n21: **Size:** M\n22: \n23: 本 AR 包含：\n24: \n25: - **包含内容：**\n26:   - Workload Manager ServiceAccount 定义\n27:   - Workload Manager ClusterRole 定义（cluster-wide 权限）\n28:   - Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding 定义\n29:   - Router ServiceAccount 定义（可选）\n30:   - Router Role 定义（namespace-scoped 权限，可选）\n31:   - Router RoleBinding 定义（可选）\n32:   - RBAC 配置验证脚本\n33:   - 使用文档和权限说明\n34: \n35: - **不包含内容：**\n36:   - Helm Chart 模板（由 AR-030 管理）\n37:   - Kubernetes 集群配置\n38:   - 应用层代码修改\n39:   - 认证/授权逻辑实现\n40: \n41: ## Current State Analysis\n42: \n43: ### 现有 RBAC 配置\n44: \n45: 根据 `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`：\n46: - Workload Manager ServiceAccount 已定义\n47: - Workload Manager ClusterRole 已定义，包含完整的 CRD、Pods、Secrets 权限\n48: - Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding 已定义\n49: \n50: 根据 `manifests/design.md`：\n51: - Router RBAC 设计为可选的 namespace-scoped Role + RoleBinding\n52: - Router 默认不创建 RBAC，通过 `router.rbac.create` 控制\n53: \n54: ### 参考设计规范\n55: \n56: 根据 `manifests/delta-spec.md` REQ-030.5 和 REQ-030.6：\n57: \n58: **Workload Manager RBAC 要求：**\n59: - ServiceAccount: `workloadmanager`，位于 release namespace\n60: - ClusterRole: `workloadmanager`，包含以下权限：\n61:   - `agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes`: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete\n62:   - `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxclaims`: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete\n63:   - `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxtemplates`: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete\n64:   - `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxwarmpools`: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete\n65:   - `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxwarmpools/status`: get, update, patch\n66:   - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters`: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete\n67:   - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters/status`: get, update, patch\n68:   - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters/finalizers`: update\n69:   - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes`: get, list, watch\n70:   - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes/status`: update, patch\n71:   - `pods`: get, list, watch\n72:   - `authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews`: create\n73:   - `secrets`: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete\n74: - ClusterRoleBinding: 绑定 ServiceAccount 到 ClusterRole\n75: \n76: **Router RBAC 要求：**\n77: - ServiceAccount: `agentcube-router`（或从 values 配置）\n78: - Role: namespace-scoped，包含 secrets 权限\n79: - RoleBinding: 绑定 ServiceAccount 到 Role\n80: - 可选：通过 `router.rbac.create` 控制是否创建\n81: \n82: ### 差距分析\n83: \n84: 1. **缺少独立 RBAC 配置** - 当前 RBAC 嵌入在 Helm Chart 中，无法单独部署\n85: 2. **缺少权限说明文档** - 未明确说明每个权限的用途和必要性\n86: 3. **缺少审计支持** - 无权限审计工具或检查清单\n87: 4. **多租户支持不完整** - 缺少针对多租户场景的 Role/RoleBinding 配置\n88: \n89: ### manifests/design.md 关键要求\n90: \n91: 1. **权限最小化** - RBAC 权限应精确到每个资源操作\n92: 2. **命名空间隔离** - Router RBAC 应为 namespace-scoped\n93: 3. **可选组件支持** - Router RBAC 默认禁用，按需启用\n94: 4. **可审计性** - RBAC 配置应易于审查和验证\n95: \n96: ## Proposed Changes\n97: \n98: ### 1. 目录结构\n99: \n100: ```\n101: manifests/rbac/\n102: ├── README.md                       # RBAC 配置说明\n103: ├── workloadmanager/\n104: │   ├── serviceaccount.yaml         # Workload Manager ServiceAccount\n105: │   ├── clusterrole.yaml            # Workload Manager ClusterRole\n106: │   └── clusterrolebinding.yaml     # Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding\n107: ├── router/\n108: │   ├── serviceaccount.yaml         # Router ServiceAccount (可选)\n109: │   ├── role.yaml                   # Router Role (可选)\n110: │   └── rolebinding.yaml            # Router RoleBinding (可选)\n111: ├── kustomization.yaml              # Kustomize 配置\n112: └── validate.sh                     # RBAC 验证脚本\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### 2. Workload Manager ServiceAccount\n116: \n117: ```yaml\n118: # manifests/rbac/workloadmanager/serviceaccount.yaml\n119: apiVersion: v1\n120: kind: ServiceAccount\n121: metadata:\n122:   name: workloadmanager\n123:   namespace: agentcube-system\n124:   labels:\n125:     app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager\n126:     app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac\n127: ---\n128: ```\n129: \n130: ### 3. Workload Manager ClusterRole\n131: \n132: ```yaml\n133: # manifests/rbac/workloadmanager/clusterrole.yaml\n134: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n135: kind: ClusterRole\n136: metadata:\n137:   name: workloadmanager\n138:   labels:\n139:     app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager\n140:     app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac\n141: rules:\n142:   # Agent Sandbox resources\n143:   - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n144:     resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n145:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n146:   \n147:   # Agent Extension resources\n148:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n149:     resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n150:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n151:   \n152:   # Warm pool status subresource\n153:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n154:     resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n155:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n156:   \n157:   # CodeInterpreter runtime resources\n158:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n159:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n160:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n161:   \n162:   # CodeInterpreter status subresource\n163:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n164:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n165:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n166:   \n167:   # CodeInterpreter finalizers\n168:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n169:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n170:     verbs: [\"update\"]\n171:   \n172:   # AgentRuntime resources (read-only)\n173:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n174:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n175:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n176:   \n177:   # AgentRuntime status subresource\n178:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n179:     resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n180:     verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n181:   \n182:   # Pod resources (read-only for status)\n183:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n184:     resources: [\"pods\"]\n185:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n186:   \n187:   # Token review for authentication\n188:   - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n189:     resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n190:     verbs: [\"create\"]\n191:   \n192:   # Secrets for credentials and configs\n193:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n194:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n195:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### 4. Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding\n199: \n200: ```yaml\n201: # manifests/rbac/workloadmanager/clusterrolebinding.yaml\n202: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n203: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n204: metadata:\n205:   name: workloadmanager\n206:   labels:\n207:     app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager\n208:     app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac\n209: subjects:\n210:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n211:     name: workloadmanager\n212:     namespace: agentcube-system\n213: roleRef:\n214:   kind: ClusterRole\n215:   name: workloadmanager\n216:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### 5. Router ServiceAccount (Optional)\n220: \n221: ```yaml\n222: # manifests/rbac/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n223: apiVersion: v1\n224: kind: ServiceAccount\n225: metadata:\n226:   name: agentcube-router\n227:   namespace: agentcube-system\n228:   labels:\n229:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router\n230:     app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac\n231:   annotations:\n232:     description: \"Optional - only required when router.rbac.create=true\"\n233: ---\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ### 6. Router Role (Optional)\n237: \n238: ```yaml\n239: # manifests/rbac/router/role.yaml\n240: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n241: kind: Role\n242: metadata:\n243:   name: agentcube-router\n244:   namespace: agentcube-system\n245:   labels:\n246:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router\n247:     app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac\n248:   annotations:\n249:     description: \"Optional - namespace-scoped RBAC for Router\"\n250: rules:\n251:   # Secrets for session tokens and credentials\n252:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n253:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n254:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n255: ```\n256: \n257: ### 7. Router RoleBinding (Optional)\n258: \n259: ```yaml\n260: # manifests/rbac/router/rolebinding.yaml\n261: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n262: kind: RoleBinding\n263: metadata:\n264:   name: agentcube-router\n265:   namespace: agentcube-system\n266:   labels:\n267:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router\n268:     app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac\n269: subjects:\n270:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n271:     name: agentcube-router\n272:     namespace: agentcube-system\n273: roleRef:\n274:   kind: Role\n275:   name: agentcube-router\n276:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n277: ```\n278: \n279: ### 8. Kustomize Configuration\n280: \n281: ```yaml\n282: # manifests/rbac/kustomization.yaml\n283: apiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1\n284: kind: Kustomization\n285: \n286: namespace: agentcube-system\n287: \n288: resources:\n289:   - workloadmanager/serviceaccount.yaml\n290:   - workloadmanager/clusterrole.yaml\n291:   - workloadmanager/clusterrolebinding.yaml\n292:   # Optional Router RBAC - uncomment to enable\n293:   # - router/serviceaccount.yaml\n294:   # - router/role.yaml\n295:   # - router/rolebinding.yaml\n296: \n297: commonLabels:\n298:   app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube\n299:   app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ### 9. RBAC 验证脚本\n303: \n304: ```bash\n305: #!/bin/bash\n306: # manifests/rbac/validate.sh\n307: \n308: set -e\n309: \n310: NAMESPACE=\"${NAMESPACE:-agentcube-system}\"\n311: \n312: echo \"Validating RBAC configuration...\"\n313: \n314: # Check Workload Manager ServiceAccount\n315: if kubectl get serviceaccount workloadmanager -n \"$NAMESPACE\" > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n316:   echo \"✓ Workload Manager ServiceAccount exists\"\n317: else\n318:   echo \"✗ Workload Manager ServiceAccount missing\"\n319:   exit 1\n320: fi\n321: \n322: # Check Workload Manager ClusterRole\n323: if kubectl get clusterrole workloadmanager > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n324:   echo \"✓ Workload Manager ClusterRole exists\"\n325: else\n326:   echo \"✗ Workload Manager ClusterRole missing\"\n327:   exit 1\n328: fi\n329: \n330: # Check Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding\n331: if kubectl get clusterrolebinding workloadmanager > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n332:   echo \"✓ Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding exists\"\n333: else\n334:   echo \"✗ Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding missing\"\n335:   exit 1\n336: fi\n337: \n338: # Verify ClusterRole permissions\n339: echo \"\"\n340: echo \"Verifying ClusterRole permissions...\"\n341: PERMISSIONS=$(kubectl get clusterrole workloadmanager -o jsonpath='{.rules[*].apiGroups[*]}')\n342: if echo \"$PERMISSIONS\" | grep -q \"agents.x-k8s.io\"; then\n343:   echo \"✓ agents.x-k8s.io API group present\"\n344: else\n345:   echo \"✗ agents.x-k8s.io API group missing\"\n346:   exit 1\n347: fi\n348: \n349: if echo \"$PERMISSIONS\" | grep -q \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"; then\n350:   echo \"✓ runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API group present\"\n351: else\n352:   echo \"✗ runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API group missing\"\n353:   exit 1\n354: fi\n355: \n356: echo \"\"\n357: echo \"RBAC validation passed!\"\n358: ```\n359: \n360: ## Impact Analysis\n361: \n362: ### 依赖影响\n363: \n364: | 依赖项 | 版本 | 用途 |\n365: |--------|------|------|\n366: | Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | RBAC API |\n367: | kubectl | ≥1.21 | 部署和验证 |\n368: | Kustomize | ≥4.0 | 配置管理 |\n369: \n370: ### 模块依赖关系\n371: \n372: ```\n373: manifests/rbac/\n374: ├── workloadmanager/\n375: │   ├── serviceaccount.yaml         # 无依赖\n376: │   ├── clusterrole.yaml            # 依赖 CRD 定义 (AR-017)\n377: │   └── clusterrolebinding.yaml     # 依赖 ServiceAccount + ClusterRole\n378: ├── router/\n379: │   ├── serviceaccount.yaml         # 无依赖\n380: │   ├── role.yaml                   # 无依赖\n381: │   └── rolebinding.yaml            # 依赖 ServiceAccount + Role\n382: ├── kustomization.yaml              # 依赖所有 RBAC 文件\n383: └── validate.sh                     # 依赖 kubectl\n384: ```\n385: \n386: ### 向后兼容性\n387: \n388: - 首次实现，无破坏性变更风险\n389: - 与 AR-030 Helm Chart 中的 RBAC 配置兼容（内容一致，组织形式不同）\n390: - 支持独立部署或与 Helm Chart 协同部署\n391: \n392: ### 测试影响\n393: \n394: - 需要验证 RBAC 权限的正确性（`kubectl auth can-i`）\n395: - 需要验证命名空间隔离（Router Role 应为 namespace-scoped）\n396: - 需要验证 ServiceAccount 与 Role/ClusterRole 的绑定关系\n397: \n398: ### 与 AR-030 的关系\n399: \n400: AR-030 的 Helm Chart 中包含的 RBAC 模板与本 AR 的独立 RBAC 配置内容一致，但使用场景不同：\n401: \n402: | 场景 | AR-030 (Helm) | AR-031 (独立) |\n403: |------|---------------|---------------|\n404: | 快速部署 | ✓ | ✗ |\n405: | 预创建权限 | ✗ | ✓ |\n406: | 权限审计 | ✗ | ✓ |\n407: | 多租户配置 | ✗ | ✓ |\n408: | 环境隔离 | 通过 values | 通过 kustomize |\n409: \n410: 推荐流程：先使用 AR-031 预创建 RBAC，再使用 AR-030 Helm Chart 部署应用。\n411: \n412: ## Alternatives Considered\n413: \n414: ### 方案 1: 仅使用 Helm Chart RBAC（不独立）\n415: \n416: **优点:**\n417: - 简单，单一部署单元\n418: - 无需额外工具\n419: \n420: **缺点:**\n421: - 无法预创建权限\n422: - 权限审计困难\n423: - 与 Helm release 绑定，难以跨环境复用\n424: \n425: **决策:** 提供独立 RBAC 配置，支持与 Helm 解耦部署。\n426: \n427: ### 方案 2: 使用 RBAC Management Operator\n428: \n429: **优点:**\n430: - 自动化 RBAC 生命周期管理\n431: - 支持动态权限调整\n432: \n433: **缺点:**\n434: - 增加运维复杂度\n435: - 需要额外的 Operator 部署\n436: \n437: **决策:** 采用静态 YAML 配置，保持简单可控。\n438: \n439: ### 方案 3: 单一巨型 RBAC 文件\n440: \n441: **优点:**\n442: - 文件数量少\n443: - 易于复制\n444: \n445: **缺点:**\n446: - 难以维护\n447: - 不支持按需启用组件\n448: \n449: **决策:** 采用模块化组织（每个组件独立目录），提高可维护性。\n450: \n451: ### 方案 4: ClusterRole vs Role 选择\n452: \n453: **Workload Manager:** 选择 ClusterRole，因为需要：\n454: - 访问跨 namespace 的 CRD\n455: - 管理多个租户的 Sandbox\n456: \n457: **Router:** 选择 Role，因为：\n458: - 仅需访问本 namespace 的 Secrets\n459: - 支持多租户隔离\n460: \n461: **决策:** 根据组件需求选择合适的 RBAC 作用域。\n462: \n463: ## Testing Strategy\n464: \n465: ### 权限验证\n466: \n467: 1. **Workload Manager 权限验证**\n468:    ```bash\n469:    kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube-system:workloadmanager\n470:    kubectl auth can-i get codeinterpreters --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube-system:workloadmanager\n471:    kubectl auth can-i update secrets --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube-system:workloadmanager\n472:    ```\n473: \n474: 2. **Router 权限验证**\n475:    ```bash\n476:    kubectl auth can-i get secrets -n agentcube-system --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube-system:agentcube-router\n477:    ```\n478: \n479: ### 隔离验证\n480: \n481: 1. **命名空间隔离** - 验证 Router Role 无法访问其他 namespace\n482: 2. **权限最小化** - 验证 RBAC 仅包含必需权限\n483: \n484: ### 集成测试\n485: \n486: 1. **Kind 集群测试** - 在 Kind 集群上实际安装验证\n487: 2. **应用联调** - 验证 Workload Manager 和 Router 能正常使用分配的权限\n488: \n489: ### 测试覆盖目标\n490: \n491: - ServiceAccount: 100%（所有组件）\n492: - ClusterRole/Role: 100%（所有权限规则）\n493: - Binding: 100%（所有绑定关系）\n494: - 验证脚本: 100%（所有检查项）\n495: \n496: ## Acceptance Criteria\n497: \n498: - [ ] Workload Manager ServiceAccount 可创建\n499: - [ ] Workload Manager ClusterRole 权限完整\n500: - [ ] Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding 正确绑定\n501: - [ ] Router ServiceAccount 可创建（可选）\n502: - [ ] Router Role 权限正确（可选）\n503: - [ ] Router RoleBinding 正确绑定（可选）\n504: - [ ] `kubectl apply -k` 成功\n505: - [ ] 验证脚本通过所有检查\n506: - [ ] 权限验证通过（`kubectl auth can-i`）\n507: - [ ] 文档完整（权限说明、使用示例）\n508: \n509: ## Dependencies\n510: \n511: ### 必需依赖\n512: - Kubernetes ≥1.21（RBAC API）\n513: - kubectl ≥1.21\n514: - Kustomize ≥4.0\n515: \n516: ### 被依赖\n517: - AR-017 (CRD 定义) - ClusterRole 权限依赖 CRD\n518: - AR-030 (Helm Chart) - 可选协同部署\n519: \n520: ## Migration Notes\n521: \n522: ### 从 Helm Chart RBAC 迁移\n523: \n524: 1. 备份现有 RBAC 配置\n525:    ```bash\n526:    kubectl get serviceaccount,clusterrole,clusterrolebinding -l app.kubernetes.io/name=workloadmanager -o yaml > backup.yaml\n527:    ```\n528: \n529: 2. 应用独立 RBAC 配置\n530:    ```bash\n531:    kubectl apply -k manifests/rbac/\n532:    ```\n533: \n534: 3. 验证权限\n535:    ```bash\n536:    ./manifests/rbac/validate.sh\n537:    ```\n538: \n539: 4. 更新 Helm Chart（可选）\n540:    - 禁用 Helm Chart 中的 RBAC 创建\n541:    - 或保留 Helm Chart RBAC（内容一致，无冲突）\n542: \n543: ### 破坏性变更\n544: 无 - 首次实现。\n545: \n546: ### 行为变更\n547: - RBAC 配置从 Helm Chart 中解耦\n548: - 支持独立部署和版本控制\n549: \n550: ## Open Questions\n551: \n552: 1. 是否需要支持自定义命名空间？（通过 kustomize namespace 字段）\n553: 2. 是否需要提供 RBAC 审计日志？（待需求明确）\n554: 3. 是否需要支持动态权限更新？（待需求明确）\n555: \n556: ## References\n557: \n558: - `manifests/design.md` - Manifests 设计文档\n559: - `manifests/delta-spec.md` - Manifests 规范（REQ-030.5, REQ-030.6）\n560: - `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` - 现有 Helm RBAC 模板\n561: - Kubernetes RBAC Best Practices: https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n562: - Kustomize Documentation: https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/manage-kubernetes-objects/kustomization/\n\n(End of file - total 562 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n\n## Purpose\n\n本提案实现 AgentCube 项目的 RBAC 配置，将 ServiceAccount、Role/ClusterRole、RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding 从 Helm Chart 模板中独立出来，形成可单独部署的 RBAC 配置模块。该 RBAC 配置是 AgentCube 控制平面组件的权限管理基础，支撑 Workload Manager 和 Router 的访问控制需求。\n\n目标是：\n\n1. **权限最小化** - 为每个组件分配精确的 RBAC 权限，遵循 least privilege 原则\n2. **模块化部署** - RBAC 配置可独立于 Helm Chart 单独部署，支持预创建权限\n3. **多租户支持** - 通过 Role/RoleBinding 支持 namespace-scoped 权限，实现多租户隔离\n4. **审计友好** - 独立的 RBAC 配置便于权限审计和安全审查\n5. **环境兼容性** - 支持开发、测试、生产环境的差异化权限配置\n\n本实现基于 manifests/design.md 和 manifests/delta-spec.md 的规范，遵循 Kubernetes RBAC 最佳实践。\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** manifests  \n**Language:** YAML  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775880971977,"end":1775880971997}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880972002,"sessionID":"ses_28540a122ffeV6GyViz90QWuux","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac1161b001I47C2t7HWmITFB","messageID":"msg_d7ac105af001G8NB658P3wtjBe","sessionID":"ses_28540a122ffeV6GyViz90QWuux","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_55b49e6861f04cb694ba3108","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** manifests  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: WorkloadManager RBAC\n11: \n12: - [ ] **T1.1** Create WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n13:   - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n14:   - Name: `workloadmanager`\n15:   - Set namespace to `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n16:   - Add standard labels (optional)\n17:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n18:   - Verify: `kubectl get sa/workloadmanager -n <namespace>` succeeds\n19: \n20: - [ ] **T1.2** Create WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n21:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRole`\n22:   - Name: `workloadmanager`\n23:   - Add rule for `agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes`: full CRUD (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete)\n24:   - Add rule for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxclaims`: full CRUD\n25:   - Add rule for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxtemplates`: full CRUD\n26:   - Add rule for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxwarmpools`: full CRUD\n27:   - Add rule for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxwarmpools/status`: get, update, patch\n28:   - Add rule for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters`: full CRUD\n29:   - Add rule for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters/status`: get, update, patch\n30:   - Add rule for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters/finalizers`: update\n31:   - Add rule for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes`: get, list, watch\n32:   - Add rule for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes/status`: update, patch\n33:   - Add rule for core `pods`: get, list, watch\n34:   - Add rule for `authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews`: create\n35:   - Add rule for core `secrets`: full CRUD\n36:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n37:   - Verify: `kubectl get clusterrole/workloadmanager` shows all rules\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T1.3** Create WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n40:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRoleBinding`\n41:   - Name: `workloadmanager`\n42:   - Reference roleRef: `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`, `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: workloadmanager`\n43:   - Reference subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: workloadmanager`, `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n44:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n45:   - Verify: `kubectl get clusterrolebinding/workloadmanager` shows correct roleRef and subjects\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## Phase 2: Router RBAC (Optional)\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.1** Create Router ServiceAccount (conditional)\n52:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}`\n53:   - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n54:   - Name: `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}`\n55:   - Set namespace to `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n56:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n57:   - Verify: ServiceAccount renders only when `router.rbac.create=true`\n58: \n59: - [ ] **T2.2** Create Router Role (namespace-scoped)\n60:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}`\n61:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: Role`\n62:   - Name: `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}`\n63:   - Namespace: `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n64:   - Add rule for core `secrets`: full CRUD (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete)\n65:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n66:   - Verify: Role is namespace-scoped (not ClusterRole)\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T2.3** Create Router RoleBinding\n69:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}`\n70:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: RoleBinding`\n71:   - Name: `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}`\n72:   - Namespace: `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n73:   - Reference roleRef: `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`, `kind: Role`, `name: <router SA name>`\n74:   - Reference subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: <router SA name>`, `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n75:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n76:   - Verify: RoleBinding connects Router SA to Router Role within namespace\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## Phase 3: Volcano Agent Scheduler RBAC (Optional)\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T3.1** Create Volcano ServiceAccount (conditional)\n83:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n84:   - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n85:   - Name: `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n86:   - Namespace: `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n87:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n88:   - Verify: ServiceAccount renders only when `volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n89: \n90: - [ ] **T3.2** Create Volcano ClusterRole\n91:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n92:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRole`\n93:   - Name: `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n94:   - Add rule for `apiextensions.k8s.io/customresourcedefinitions`: create, get, list, watch, delete\n95:   - Add rule for core `events`: create, list, watch, update, patch\n96:   - Add rule for core `pods`: get, list, watch, patch, delete\n97:   - Add rule for core `pods/status`: update\n98:   - Add rule for core `pods/binding`: create\n99:   - Add rule for core `persistentvolumeclaims`: list, watch, update\n100:   - Add rule for core `persistentvolumes`: list, watch, update\n101:   - Add rule for core `namespaces`: list, watch, get\n102:   - Add rule for core `services`: list, watch, get\n103:   - Add rule for core `replicationcontrollers`: list, watch, get\n104:   - Add rule for core `resourcequotas`: list, watch\n105:   - Add rule for core `nodes`: get, list, watch, update, patch\n106:   - Add rule for `storage.k8s.io/storageclasses`: list, watch\n107:   - Add rule for `storage.k8s.io/csinodes`: list, watch\n108:   - Add rule for `storage.k8s.io/csidrivers`: list, watch\n109:   - Add rule for `storage.k8s.io/csistoragecapacities`: list, watch\n110:   - Add rule for `storage.k8s.io/volumeattachments`: list, watch\n111:   - Add rule for `policy/poddisruptionbudgets`: list, watch\n112:   - Add rule for `scheduling.k8s.io/priorityclasses`: get, list, watch\n113:   - Add rule for `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io/podgroups`: list, watch, update\n114:   - Add rule for `scheduling.volcano.sh/podgroups`: list, watch, update\n115:   - Add rule for core `configmaps`: get, list, watch, create, delete, update\n116:   - Add rule for `apps/daemonsets`: list, watch, get\n117:   - Add rule for `apps/replicasets`: list, watch, get\n118:   - Add rule for `apps/statefulsets`: list, watch, get\n119:   - Add rule for `coordination.k8s.io/leases`: get, create, update, watch\n120:   - Add rule for `resource.k8s.io/resourceclaims`: get, list, watch, create, update, patch\n121:   - Add rule for `resource.k8s.io/resourceclaims/status`: update\n122:   - Add rule for `resource.k8s.io/deviceclasses`: get, list, watch, create\n123:   - Add rule for `resource.k8s.io/resourceslices`: get, list, watch, create\n124:   - Add rule for `shard.volcano.sh/nodeshards`: list, watch, get, update\n125:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n126:   - Verify: ClusterRole has comprehensive scheduling permissions\n127: \n128: - [ ] **T3.3** Create Volcano ClusterRoleBinding\n129:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n130:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRoleBinding`\n131:   - Name: `volcano-agent-scheduler-role`\n132:   - Reference roleRef: `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`, `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n133:   - Reference subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`, `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n134:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n135:   - Verify: Binding connects Volcano SA to ClusterRole\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## Phase 4: RBAC Validation\n140: \n141: - [ ] **T4.1** Test WorkloadManager RBAC with helm template\n142:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\"`\n143:   - Verify: ServiceAccount/workloadmanager present in output\n144:   - Verify: ClusterRole/workloadmanager present with all rules\n145:   - Verify: ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager present with correct references\n146: \n147: - [ ] **T4.2** Test Router RBAC disabled by default\n148:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\"`\n149:   - Verify: No Router ServiceAccount in output\n150:   - Verify: No Router Role in output\n151:   - Verify: No Router RoleBinding in output\n152: \n153: - [ ] **T4.3** Test Router RBAC enabled\n154:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true`\n155:   - Verify: ServiceAccount/agentcube-router present\n156:   - Verify: Role/agentcube-router present with secrets permissions\n157:   - Verify: RoleBinding/agentcube-router present\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T4.4** Test Router RBAC with custom serviceAccountName\n160:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=custom-router`\n161:   - Verify: ServiceAccount/custom-router present\n162:   - Verify: Role/custom-router present\n163:   - Verify: RoleBinding/custom-router present with correct references\n164: \n165: - [ ] **T4.5** Test Volcano RBAC disabled by default\n166:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\"`\n167:   - Verify: No Volcano ServiceAccount in output\n168:   - Verify: No Volcano ClusterRole in output\n169:   - Verify: No Volcano ClusterRoleBinding in output\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T4.6** Test Volcano RBAC enabled\n172:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n173:   - Verify: ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler present\n174:   - Verify: ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler present with scheduling permissions\n175:   - Verify: ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role present\n176: \n177: - [ ] **T4.7** Validate YAML syntax\n178:   - Command: `helm lint manifests/charts/base`\n179:   - Verify: No RBAC-related errors or warnings\n180: \n181: - [ ] **T4.8** Apply RBAC to test cluster (optional)\n182:   - Command: `kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml --namespace=test`\n183:   - Command: `kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml --namespace=test` (with values override)\n184:   - Command: `kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml --namespace=test` (with values override)\n185:   - Verify: All RBAC resources created successfully\n186: \n187: - [ ] **T4.9** Verify WorkloadManager permissions\n188:   - Command: `kubectl auth can-i --as=system:serviceaccount:<namespace>:workloadmanager --list --namespace=test`\n189:   - Verify: Expected permissions listed for sandboxes, codeinterpreters, secrets, etc.\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T4.10** Verify Router permissions (when enabled)\n192:   - Command: `kubectl auth can-i --as=system:serviceaccount:<namespace>:agentcube-router --list --namespace=test`\n193:   - Verify: Secrets CRUD permissions in namespace\n194: \n195: - [ ] **T4.11** Verify Volcano permissions (when enabled)\n196:   - Command: `kubectl auth can-i --as=system:serviceaccount:<namespace>:volcano-agent-scheduler --list --namespace=test`\n197:   - Verify: Scheduling permissions for pods, nodes, podgroups, etc.\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## Acceptance Criteria\n202: \n203: 1. ✅ WorkloadManager ServiceAccount created in release namespace\n204: 2. ✅ WorkloadManager ClusterRole has full CRUD for sandbox-related CRDs\n205: 3. ✅ WorkloadManager ClusterRole has status update permissions for codeinterpreters and agentruntimes\n206: 4. ✅ WorkloadManager ClusterRole has finalizer update permission for codeinterpreters\n207: 5. ✅ WorkloadManager ClusterRole has tokenreviews create for authentication\n208: 6. ✅ WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding correctly binds SA to ClusterRole\n209: 7. ✅ Router RBAC is optional (disabled by default)\n210: 8. ✅ Router RBAC uses namespace-scoped Role (not ClusterRole)\n211: 9. ✅ Router RBAC limited to secrets management\n212: 10. ✅ Router serviceAccountName is configurable via values\n213: 11. ✅ Volcano RBAC is optional (disabled by default)\n214: 12. ✅ Volcano ClusterRole has comprehensive scheduling permissions\n215: 13. ✅ Volcano ClusterRoleBinding correctly binds SA to ClusterRole\n216: 14. ✅ All conditional rendering works correctly via helm template\n217: 15. ✅ `helm lint` passes with no RBAC-related errors\n218: 16. ✅ RBAC resources apply successfully to test cluster\n219: 17. ✅ `kubectl auth can-i` confirms expected permissions for each SA\n220: 18. ✅ RBAC follows least-privilege principle (each SA has only necessary permissions)\n221: 19. ✅ All manifests use Helm templating for namespace consistency\n222: 20. ✅ RBAC configuration matches AR-030 Phase 6 and Phase 7 specifications\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: **Notes:**\n227: - Stage ST-3: Implementation complete (templates exist in codebase)\n228: - WorkloadManager RBAC: Always installed (core component)\n229: - Router RBAC: Optional, controlled by `router.rbac.create` (default: false)\n230: - Volcano RBAC: Optional, controlled by `volcano.scheduler.enabled` (default: false)\n231: - WorkloadManager uses ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding (cluster-wide permissions required)\n232: - Router uses Role/RoleBinding (namespace-scoped, secrets only)\n233: - Volcano uses ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding (cluster-wide scheduling permissions)\n234: - All templates use `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` for namespace consistency\n235: - Router serviceAccountName configurable via `router.serviceAccountName` values key\n\n(End of file - total 235 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Tasks\n\n**Module:** manifests  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: WorkloadManager RBAC\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n  - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n  - Name: `workloadmanager`\n  - Set namespace to `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - Add standard labels (optional)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verify: `kubectl get sa/workloadmanager -n <namespace>` succeeds\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Create WorkloadManager ClusterRole","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775880971980,"end":1775880972000}}}}
