{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881018997,"sessionID":"ses_28540a122ffeV6GyViz90QWuux","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac1d9a50010oqBMH5ay7mLBy","messageID":"msg_d7ac1d006001tq4YlaSSOAzPkf","sessionID":"ses_28540a122ffeV6GyViz90QWuux","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9759eb2b21a34373acc2159d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `manifests`  \n6: **Language:** YAML  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Standalone RBAC manifests for ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** manifests/delta-spec.md (AR-030), manifests/design.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-031.1: ServiceAccount Manifests\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ServiceAccount manifests for WorkloadManager, Router, and Volcano Scheduler components.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount creation\n21: - **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` is applied\n22: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` is executed\n23: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount metadata\n26: - **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n27: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n28: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n29:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n30:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n31:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: control-plane`\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount creation\n34: - **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/router.yaml` is applied\n35: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/router.yaml` is executed\n36: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount metadata\n39: - **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n40: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n41: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n42:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n43:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n44:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: control-plane`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount creation\n47: - **GIVEN** the manifest `serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is applied\n48: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is executed\n49: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount metadata\n52: - **GIVEN** the manifest is applied\n53: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n55:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n56:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n57:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: volcano-agent-scheduler`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: scheduler`\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ### REQ-031.2: ClusterRole Manifests\n62: \n63: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ClusterRole manifests defining permissions for WorkloadManager and Volcano Scheduler.\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole creation\n66: - **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` is applied\n67: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` is executed\n68: - **THEN** a ClusterRole named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole sandbox permissions\n71: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n72: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n74:   - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n75:   - `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`\n76:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole extension resources\n79: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n80: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n82:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n83:   - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n84:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole warm pool status\n87: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n88: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n89: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n90:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n91:   - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n92:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n95: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n96: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n98:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n99:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n100:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n101:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]`, `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n102:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]`, `verbs: [\"update\"]`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole AgentRuntime permissions\n105: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n106: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n107: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n108:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n109:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]`\n110:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n111:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]`\n112:   - `verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]`\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole core resources\n115: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n116: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n117: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n118:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n119:   - `resources: [\"pods\", \"secrets\"]`\n120:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole token review\n123: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n124: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n125: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n126:   - `apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]`\n127:   - `resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]`\n128:   - `verbs: [\"create\"]`\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole creation\n131: - **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is applied\n132: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is executed\n133: - **THEN** a ClusterRole named `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL be created\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole CRD permissions\n136: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n137: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n138: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n139:   - `apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]`\n140:   - `resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]`\n141:   - `verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]`\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole pod permissions\n144: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n145: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL include comprehensive pod permissions:\n147:   - `resources: [\"pods\", \"pods/status\", \"pods/binding\", \"pods/disruptionbudgets\"]`\n148:   - `resources: [\"persistentvolumeclaims\", \"persistentvolumes\"]`\n149:   - `resources: [\"nodes\", \"namespaces\", \"services\", \"replicationcontrollers\"]`\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole scheduling permissions\n152: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n153: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n154: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n155:   - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.k8s.io\"]`\n156:   - `resources: [\"priorityclasses\"]`\n157:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n158:   - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.incubator.k8s.io\", \"scheduling.volcano.sh\"]`\n159:   - `resources: [\"podgroups\"]`\n160:   - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\", \"update\"]`\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole storage permissions\n163: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n164: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n165: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n166:   - `apiGroups: [\"storage.k8s.io\"]`\n167:   - `resources: [\"storageclasses\", \"csinodes\", \"csidrivers\", \"csistoragecapacities\", \"volumeattachments\"]`\n168:   - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\"]`\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole configmap permissions\n171: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRole is created\n172: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n173: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n174:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n175:   - `resources: [\"configmaps\"]`\n176:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"delete\", \"update\"]`\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ### REQ-031.3: ClusterRoleBinding Manifests\n181: \n182: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ClusterRoleBinding manifests binding ClusterRoles to ServiceAccounts.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding creation\n185: - **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml` is applied\n186: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml` is executed\n187: - **THEN** a ClusterRoleBinding named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding subject\n190: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n191: - **WHEN** subjects are validated\n192: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n193:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n194:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n195:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding roleRef\n198: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n199: - **WHEN** roleRef is validated\n200: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n201:   - `kind: ClusterRole`\n202:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n203:   - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding creation\n206: - **GIVEN** the manifest `clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is applied\n207: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml` is executed\n208: - **THEN** a ClusterRoleBinding named `volcano-agent-scheduler-role` SHALL be created\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding subject\n211: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n212: - **WHEN** subjects are validated\n213: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n214:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n215:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n216:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding roleRef\n219: - **GIVEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is created\n220: - **WHEN** roleRef is validated\n221: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n222:   - `kind: ClusterRole`\n223:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n224:   - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ### REQ-031.4: Role Manifests (Namespace-Scoped)\n229: \n230: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide namespace-scoped Role manifests for Router component.\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Router Role creation\n233: - **GIVEN** the manifest `roles/router.yaml` is applied\n234: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f roles/router.yaml` is executed\n235: - **THEN** a Role named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Router Role secret permissions\n238: - **GIVEN** the Role is created\n239: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n240: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n241:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n242:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n243:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Router Role configmap permissions\n246: - **GIVEN** the Role is created\n247: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n248: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n249:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n250:   - `resources: [\"configmaps\"]`\n251:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Router Role pod permissions\n254: - **GIVEN** the Role is created\n255: - **WHEN** rules are validated\n256: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n257:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n258:   - `resources: [\"pods\"]`\n259:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ### REQ-031.5: RoleBinding Manifests (Namespace-Scoped)\n264: \n265: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide namespace-scoped RoleBinding manifests binding Roles to ServiceAccounts.\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding creation\n268: - **GIVEN** the manifest `rolebindings/router.yaml` is applied\n269: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f rolebindings/router.yaml` is executed\n270: - **THEN** a RoleBinding named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created in the target namespace\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding subject\n273: - **GIVEN** the RoleBinding is created\n274: - **WHEN** subjects are validated\n275: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n276:   - `kind: ServiceAccount`\n277:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n278:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}` (or target namespace)\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding roleRef\n281: - **GIVEN** the RoleBinding is created\n282: - **WHEN** roleRef is validated\n283: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n284:   - `kind: Role`\n285:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n286:   - `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n287: \n288: ---\n289: \n290: ### REQ-031.6: Namespace Management\n291: \n292: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide namespace manifest and support namespace creation before RBAC application.\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: Namespace manifest creation\n295: - **GIVEN** the manifest `namespace.yaml` is applied\n296: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f namespace.yaml` is executed\n297: - **THEN** a namespace named `agentcube-system` SHALL be created\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: Namespace metadata\n300: - **GIVEN** the namespace is created\n301: - **WHEN** namespace is validated\n302: - **THEN** it SHALL include labels:\n303:   - `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube`\n304:   - `app.kubernetes.io/component: control-plane`\n305: \n306: #### Scenario: Custom namespace support\n307: - **GIVEN** user wants to use custom namespace\n308: - **WHEN** manifests are applied with `--namespace` flag\n309: - **THEN** all RBAC resources SHALL be created in the specified namespace\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Default namespace fallback\n312: - **GIVEN** no namespace is specified\n313: - **WHEN** manifests are applied\n314: - **THEN** resources SHALL be created in `agentcube-system` namespace (from manifest) or `default` namespace\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ### REQ-031.7: Combined RBAC Manifest\n319: \n320: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a combined RBAC manifest that applies all RBAC resources in correct order.\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: Combined manifest existence\n323: - **GIVEN** the manifest `rbac.yaml` exists\n324: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f rbac.yaml` is executed\n325: - **THEN** all ServiceAccounts, ClusterRoles, ClusterRoleBindings, Roles, and RoleBindings SHALL be created\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Correct resource ordering\n328: - **GIVEN** the combined manifest is applied\n329: - **WHEN** resources are created\n330: - **THEN** order SHALL be:\n331:   1. ServiceAccounts\n332:   2. ClusterRoles\n333:   3. ClusterRoleBindings\n334:   4. Roles\n335:   5. RoleBindings\n336: \n337: #### Scenario: Combined manifest labels\n338: - **GIVEN** the combined manifest is applied\n339: - **WHEN** resources are created\n340: - **THEN** all resources SHALL include common label:\n341:   - `app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac`\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ### REQ-031.8: RBAC Validation and Verification\n346: \n347: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide validation scripts and commands to verify RBAC configuration.\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: RBAC validation script\n350: - **GIVEN** the script `validate-rbac.sh` exists\n351: - **WHEN** `./validate-rbac.sh` is executed\n352: - **THEN** script SHALL verify all ServiceAccounts exist\n353: \n354: #### Scenario: ClusterRole permissions check\n355: - **GIVEN** the validation script is executed\n356: - **WHEN** ClusterRoles are checked\n357: - **THEN** script SHALL verify all required permissions are present\n358: \n359: #### Scenario: Binding verification\n360: - **GIVEN** the validation script is executed\n361: - **WHEN** bindings are checked\n362: - **THEN** script SHALL verify all ServiceAccounts are bound to correct roles\n363: \n364: #### Scenario: RBAC verification report\n365: - **GIVEN** the validation script completes\n366: - **WHEN** report is generated\n367: - **THEN** output SHALL include:\n368:   - List of all ServiceAccounts\n369:   - List of all ClusterRoles with permission counts\n370:   - List of all bindings with subjects\n371: \n372: ---\n373: \n374: ### REQ-031.9: Multi-Namespace Support\n375: \n376: **Requirement:** The system SHALL support deploying RBAC for multiple namespaces.\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: Multi-namespace ServiceAccount\n379: - **GIVEN** manifests are applied to multiple namespaces\n380: - **WHEN** `kubectl apply -f serviceaccounts/ -n namespace1` and `-n namespace2` are executed\n381: - **THEN** ServiceAccounts SHALL be created in both namespaces\n382: \n383: #### Scenario: ClusterRole reuse across namespaces\n384: - **GIVEN** ClusterRoles are cluster-scoped\n385: - **WHEN** multiple namespaces use the same Component\n386: - **THEN** single ClusterRole SHALL be shared across namespaces\n387: \n388: #### Scenario: Namespace-specific RoleBindings\n389: - **GIVEN** multiple namespaces are configured\n390: - **WHEN** RoleBindings are created\n391: - **THEN** each namespace SHALL have its own RoleBinding referencing namespace-specific ServiceAccount\n392: \n393: ---\n394: \n395: ### REQ-031.10: RBAC Cleanup\n396: \n397: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide cleanup manifests and scripts to remove RBAC resources.\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: RBAC cleanup manifest\n400: - **GIVEN** the manifest `rbac-cleanup.yaml` exists\n401: - **WHEN** `kubectl delete -f rbac-cleanup.yaml` is executed\n402: - **THEN** all RBAC resources SHALL be deleted\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: Correct cleanup ordering\n405: - **GIVEN** cleanup is executed\n406: - **WHEN** resources are deleted\n407: - **THEN** order SHALL be:\n408:   1. RoleBindings\n409:   2. Roles\n410:   3. ClusterRoleBindings\n411:   4. ClusterRoles\n412:   5. ServiceAccounts\n413: \n414: #### Scenario: Namespace-preserved cleanup\n415: - **GIVEN** cleanup is executed with `--preserve-namespace`\n416: - **WHEN** resources are deleted\n417: - **THEN** namespace SHALL NOT be deleted, only RBAC resources\n418: \n419: ---\n420: \n421: ## Data Types\n422: \n423: ```yaml\n424: # ServiceAccount structure\n425: serviceAccount:\n426:   apiVersion: v1\n427:   kind: ServiceAccount\n428:   metadata:\n429:     name: string\n430:     namespace: string\n431:     labels:\n432:       app.kubernetes.io/name: string\n433:       app.kubernetes.io/component: string\n434: \n435: # ClusterRole structure\n436: clusterRole:\n437:   apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n438:   kind: ClusterRole\n439:   metadata:\n440:     name: string\n441:   rules:\n442:     - apiGroups: [string]\n443:       resources: [string]\n444:       verbs: [string]\n445: \n446: # ClusterRoleBinding structure\n447: clusterRoleBinding:\n448:   apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n449:   kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n450:   metadata:\n451:     name: string\n452:   roleRef:\n453:     kind: ClusterRole\n454:     name: string\n455:     apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n456:   subjects:\n457:     - kind: ServiceAccount\n458:       name: string\n459:       namespace: string\n460: \n461: # Role structure (namespace-scoped)\n462: role:\n463:   apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n464:   kind: Role\n465:   metadata:\n466:     name: string\n467:     namespace: string\n468:   rules:\n469:     - apiGroups: [string]\n470:       resources: [string]\n471:       verbs: [string]\n472: \n473: # RoleBinding structure (namespace-scoped)\n474: roleBinding:\n475:   apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n476:   kind: RoleBinding\n477:   metadata:\n478:     name: string\n479:     namespace: string\n480:   roleRef:\n481:     kind: Role\n482:     name: string\n483:     apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n484:   subjects:\n485:     - kind: ServiceAccount\n486:       name: string\n487:       namespace: string\n488: ```\n489: \n490: ---\n491: \n492: ## File Structure\n493: \n494: ```\n495: manifests/rbac/\n496: ├── README.md\n497: ├── namespace.yaml\n498: ├── serviceaccounts/\n499: │   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n500: │   ├── router.yaml\n501: │   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n502: ├── clusterroles/\n503: │   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n504: │   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n505: ├── clusterrolebindings/\n506: │   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n507: │   └── volcano-scheduler.yaml\n508: ├── roles/\n509: │   └── router.yaml\n510: ├── rolebindings/\n511: │   └── router.yaml\n512: ├── rbac.yaml              # Combined manifest\n513: ├── rbac-cleanup.yaml      # Cleanup manifest\n514: └── validate-rbac.sh       # Validation script\n515: ```\n516: \n517: ---\n518: \n519: ## Environment Variables\n520: \n521: | Variable | Description | Default |\n522: |----------|-------------|---------|\n523: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | Target namespace for RBAC resources | `agentcube-system` |\n524: | `KUBECONFIG` | Kubernetes config file | `~/.kube/config` |\n525: \n526: ---\n527: \n528: ## Error Codes\n529: \n530: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n531: |-------|-----------|---------|\n532: | Namespace not found | 1 | `Namespace '{namespace}' does not exist. Run: kubectl apply -f namespace.yaml` |\n533: | ServiceAccount not found | 1 | `ServiceAccount '{name}' not found in namespace '{namespace}'` |\n534: | ClusterRole not found | 1 | `ClusterRole '{name}' not found` |\n535: | Binding failure | 1 | `Failed to bind {role} to {serviceAccount}: {detail}` |\n536: | Permission denied | 1 | `RBAC: User '{user}' cannot {verb} {resource}` |\n537: | Invalid manifest syntax | 1 | `YAML parse error in {file}: {detail}` |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Dependencies\n542: \n543: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n544: |---------|---------|---------|\n545: | Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | RBAC API (rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1) |\n546: | kubectl | ≥1.21 | Manifest application and validation |\n547: \n548: ---\n549: \n550: ## Acceptance Checklist\n551: \n552: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/namespace.yaml` — Namespace manifest with correct labels\n553: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n554: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/router.yaml` — Router ServiceAccount\n555: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/serviceaccounts/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount\n556: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterroles/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ClusterRole with all permissions\n557: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterroles/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole with scheduling permissions\n558: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/workloadmanager.yaml` — WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n559: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/clusterrolebindings/volcano-scheduler.yaml` — Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n560: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/roles/router.yaml` — Router Role (namespace-scoped)\n561: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/rolebindings/router.yaml` — Router RoleBinding\n562: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/rbac.yaml` — Combined manifest with correct ordering\n563: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/rbac-cleanup.yaml` — Cleanup manifest with reverse ordering\n564: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/validate-rbac.sh` — Validation script\n565: - [ ] `manifests/rbac/README.md` — Usage documentation\n566: - [ ] `kubectl apply -f manifests/rbac/` succeeds without errors\n567: - [ ] Validation script reports all resources as healthy\n568: - [ ] Cleanup removes all RBAC resources correctly\n569: - [ ] Multi-namespace deployment works correctly\n570: \n571: ---\n572: \n573: ## Open Questions\n574: \n575: 1. Should RBAC manifests support fine-grained permission customization through overlay files?\n576: 2. Should the validation script integrate with CI/CD pipelines for automated RBAC testing?\n577: 3. Should RBAC manifests include PodSecurityPolicy or PodSecurityStandard bindings?\n578: 4. Should there be separate RBAC profiles (minimal, standard, full) for different security requirements?\n\n(End of file - total 578 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Standalone RBAC manifests for ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding\n\n**Base Specs:** manifests/delta-spec.md (AR-030), manifests/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-031.1: ServiceAccount Manifests\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide standalone ServiceAccount manifests for WorkloadManager, Router, and Volcano Scheduler components.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ServiceAccount creation","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775881018981,"end":1775881018994}}}}
